Roles & Permissions Spec (Java Backend – Centralized Policy)

Scope

This document locks the authorization model for the Merchant Admin (internal portal) and related backend APIs.

It defines:
	•	Roles: ADMIN, STAFF, EDITOR
	•	Actions (permissions) as stable backend constants
	•	Plan/module gating via Capabilities
	•	Tenant isolation rules
	•	Enforcement pattern: centralized policy (Option B)

⸻

1) Principles

1.1 Tenant isolation is non-negotiable

All permissions are evaluated within a tenant scope.

A user may belong to multiple tenants, but:
	•	A token is valid for exactly one tenant (the tenant that issued the token).
	•	Every request must be authorized for the target {tenantId}.

1.2 Centralized policy is the only authorization source of truth

Controllers/services do not check roles directly.

They call:
	•	policy.require(authCtx, Action.X, TenantScope(tenantId))

1.3 Roles are coarse; Actions are stable

We do not authorize by endpoint name. We authorize by business action.

1.4 Capabilities gate features by plan

Even if a role allows an action, the tenant must have the required module enabled.

⸻

2) Roles (locked)

ADMIN
	•	Full access to everything in the tenant.
	•	Only role allowed to manage: payment settings, domains, staff management, tenant settings, publishing.

STAFF
	•	Daily operations role.
	•	Can manage: products, categories, pricing, product media, scheduling, orders/sales, refunds.
	•	Cannot edit site pages and cannot publish.
	•	Cannot modify sensitive tenant/platform settings.

EDITOR
	•	Content/site role.
	•	Can edit predefined site/page data (via Merchant Admin “Site” UI).
	•	Cannot publish.
	•	No access to store, orders, scheduling, domains, payments, staff.

⸻

3) Action Catalog (locked)

These are the canonical permission “verbs” used across the Java backend.

3.1 Site
	•	SITE_EDIT — edit site/pages via Merchant Admin UI
	•	SITE_PUBLISH — publish content changes (admin-only)

3.2 Store (Catalog)
	•	PRODUCT_MANAGE — create/edit/archive products
	•	CATEGORY_MANAGE — create/edit/archive categories and ordering
	•	PRICING_MANAGE — set price (simple price_cents) and compare_at (if added later)
	•	PRODUCT_MEDIA_MANAGE — upload/manage product images (Option A, Java owns images)

3.3 Orders / Selling (ops)
	•	ORDER_VIEW — view orders
	•	ORDER_MANAGE — change order lifecycle states (excluding refunds if you prefer to separate)
	•	REFUND_MANAGE — issue/refund actions (STAFF allowed)
	•	SALE_CREATE — create “admin sale” / POS/manual order entry

3.4 Scheduling (Pro)
	•	SERVICE_MANAGE — manage services
	•	BOOKING_MANAGE — manage bookings

3.5 Admin/Platform Settings (sensitive)
	•	PAYMENT_SETTINGS_MANAGE — configure Wompi keys, enable payment methods (admin-only)
	•	DOMAIN_MANAGE — domain statuses, renewal ops (admin-only)
	•	STAFF_MANAGE — invite/disable members, role changes (admin-only)
	•	TENANT_SETTINGS_MANAGE — template/plan toggles, high-level settings (admin-only)

⸻

4) Role → Action Matrix (locked)

ADMIN
	•	Allowed actions: ALL (*) within the tenant

STAFF

Allowed:
	•	Store: PRODUCT_MANAGE, CATEGORY_MANAGE, PRICING_MANAGE, PRODUCT_MEDIA_MANAGE
	•	Orders/Selling: ORDER_VIEW, ORDER_MANAGE, SALE_CREATE, REFUND_MANAGE
	•	Scheduling: SERVICE_MANAGE, BOOKING_MANAGE

Not allowed:
	•	Site: SITE_EDIT, SITE_PUBLISH
	•	Admin settings: PAYMENT_SETTINGS_MANAGE, DOMAIN_MANAGE, STAFF_MANAGE, TENANT_SETTINGS_MANAGE

EDITOR

Allowed:
	•	Site: SITE_EDIT

Not allowed:
	•	SITE_PUBLISH
	•	All store/orders/scheduling/admin-settings actions

